=====================================================================================Step:01:Install Local Windows Aws Cli======================================================
Search For Install The AWS Command Line Interface On Microsoft Windows,DownLoad Appropriate Msi Installer Of Os Architechture Type[32/64].For Mine I Have Used Following Url:
https://s3.amazonaws.com/aws-cli/AWSCLI64.msi & Install It.Also We Can Use Amazon Linux AMI [2018.03.0 (HVM), SSD Volume Type,Latest One] On A t2.micro.These Ami Comes With
Aws Cli Pre-Installed[Follow Step:2].Type aws To Validate Cli Is Installed Using PowerShell.
=====================================================================================Step:02:Role Creation For Aws Cli In Ec2===================================================
1.Create A Role.GoTo Identity and Access Management->Roles->Create Role->Select type of trusted entity[AWS service]->Select EC2->Search For Policy Type,With Search KeyWord 
Admin->Select AdministratorAccess Policy->Give Role name AdministratorAccessForEc2ServiceRole->Create Role.
2.Goto EC2 Dashboard->Create Instance[Launch Instance]->Choose an Amazon Machine Image (AMI)->Chosse Any Free Tier Eligible Linux AMI[i.e:Amazon Linux AMI 2018.03.0 (HVM), 
SSD Volume Type - ami-64260718]->Next->Choose an Instance Type[t2.micro]->Configure Instance Details->IAM role[AdministratorAccessForEc2ServiceRole],Check Auto-assign Public 
IP Is Enabled.->Add Storage[Default Will Suffice]->Give Tag For Billing Identification/Cost Allocation[Name:Ec2ForAwsCli,BillCategory:LearnAwsCli],These Are Optional.->
Configure Security Group,Create a new security group[SecurityGroupAwsCli]->Add Ssh Rule For Source Anywhere[We Will Add Other Protocol/Port If Required].->Review Instance 
Launch->Create A New Key Pair[AwsCliEc2KeyPair] & DownLoad It[Don't Share In Public]->Launch Instance->Find Public Ip In IPv4 Public IP Section In Description Section.
My Public Ip Will Be Used For Ssh Access.We Are Not Going To Use This Instance Right Now,So We Can Stop It For Now.
=====================================================================================Step:03:Ec2 AwsCli MobaXTerm===============================================================
Download & Install MobaXTerm->Click On Session->Click On Ssh->Provide Your Ec2 Instance Public Ip[54.255.167.121] In Remote Host,Check Specify Username[ec2-user]->Goto 
Advanced Ssh Settings,Check Use Private Key[Select AwsCliEc2KeyPair.pem],Click Ok.Save This Session If You Wish.
Do A sudo yum update To Get Latest Patch/Update & Once Done Type aws To Validate Cli Is Already Installed Using Ssh Terminal.
Do aws configure,Keep AWS Access Key ID,AWS Secret Access Key As Blank  As Ec2 Launched With Apprpriate Role,Default region name:Ec2 Launch Region[ap-southeast-1],Default 
output format:Default Is Json,No Need To Provide.
Now Do  curl http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/iam/security-credentials/AdministratorAccessForEc2ServiceRole: Will Return Something Like This[For Security Reason 
AccessKeyId/SecretAccessKey/Token Are Obfuscated]:
{
  "Code" : "Success",
  "LastUpdated" : "2018-04-28T17:00:25Z",
  "Type" : "AWS-HMAC",
  "AccessKeyId" : "XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX",
  "SecretAccessKey" : "XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX",
  "Token" : "XXXXXXX//////////XXXXXXX+XXXXXXX/XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX/XXXXXXX/XXXXXXX/XXXXXXX/XXXXXXX+XXXXXXX/XXXXXXX/XXXXXXX/XXXXXXX+XXXXXXX",
  "Expiration" : "2018-04-28T23:31:29Z"
}
Also Checkout Other Aws Command Like:aws ec2 describe-instances.
N.B:We Can Also Setup Profiles In ~/.aws/credentials With AccessKeyId & SecretAccessKey[That Will Be Part Of Advanced Tutorial] & Use --profile To Mention Which Profile To Use.
But Switch Roles Using Cli,You Need To Use Static Credential[AccessKeyId,SecretAccessKey] Stored In ~/.aws/credentials File.
